      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "All are on debut and each of them has either won or placed at the trials. GOCCIADORO (6) is a two-year-old colt by Downbytheseaside from the Nathan Jack yard. Draws widest in the small field but looks to have talent having easily won his latest trial at Melton. ELECTRICUTE (4) is by Captain Crunch and hails from the David Hewitt stable. Has strong trial form coming into this, winning his hitout at Goulburn. Anticipating a bright start to his career. ARMA LINCOLN (1) is a colt by For A Reason form the Neil Day yard. Runner-up in both trials and the ace draw is an aid to an inexperienced juvenile. Brett Woodhouse's Art Major colt HEAR NO EVIL (2) has been trialling well and draws to be competitive.",
